green beans in black bean sauce

1 lb green beans
2 garlic cloves minced
2 tbsp black bean paste
2 tbsp soy sauce
1/4 c water
1 tbsp corn starch (maybe less)

wash green beans, cut to bite size pieces.
mix black bean paste, soy sauce, water and corn starch until smooth.
heat wok and water to medium heat and cook the garlic and beans (2mins).
Add sauce to the beans stirring constantly to coat beans.
sauce will get think.
serve hot over rice.
